18_SAS_On What is SAAS.


Q1
What is software as a service?
ANS
SOFTWARE AS A SERVICE - METHOD OF SOFTWARE DELIVERY WHICH ALLOWS DATA TO BE ACCESSED FROM ANY DEVICE WITH AN INTERNET CONNECTION THROUGH A BROWSER.
Q2
In the web based model software vendors host and maintain servers, databases, and the core that constitute the application. True/False?
ANS
TRUE
Q3
How is web based software model different from on premise software model?
ANS
ON PREMISE - CLOUD BASED

COMPANIES DONâ€™T HAVE TO INVEST IN EXTENSIVE HARDWARE TO HOST THE SOFTWARE AND THIS IN TURN ALLOWS BUYERS TO OUTSOURCE MOST OF THE IT RESPONSIBILITIES.

THE SAAS PROVIDER WILL TAKE CARE OF EVERYTHING, INCLUDING THE SOFTWARE THIS TIME.

DELIVERY THROUGH INTERNET WITH WEB BROWSER, INFRASTRUCTURE HOSTED AND MANAGED BY SOFTWARE / THIRD-PARTY SERVICE PROVIDER

VS ON PREMISE SOFTWARE INSTALLED AND OPERATED ON LOCAL INFRA, OWNED AND MAINTAINED BY ORG WITH FULL CONTROL OVER HARDWARE, SOFTWARE, INFRA.

LIMITED CUSTOMIZATION VS EXTENSIVE CUSTOMIZATION.

AND MORE.
